item.title: Index
item.description: Abdu Murray speaking about Western culture. "Confusion is lauded as a virtue. Clarity is decried as if it was a sin. Because if you are confused sexually you're a hero; if you're confused morally you're a progressive; if you're confused religiously, you're tolerant. If you're clear on any of those things, you're a bigot, regressive, or intolerant." Abdu Murray, Stand to Reason podcast (~7 mins), May 4th 2018. Previous Next
